ior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/10/02 11:52:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jnaggy291392mi/EQ/bubbles1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Question on 2-handers please</span><hr size=1> I have to admit I am kind of 2-hander newbie.<br>
<br>
I know that a fairly long time ago, they adjusted 2-handers damage bonus so that the slower the weapon, the better the damage bonus.<br>
<br>
My question is this:<br>
<br>
Do 2 handers become more, and more superior to dual weilding the more haste you have due to the added damage bonus?<br>
<br>
I ask because with my standard parsing I never have anything other than item haste ( /cry 26%), and I do not see as much of a DPS increase from a 2-hander as most claim I should.<br>
<br>
I realise that the answer is yes, obviously, but is it a rather obvious scale is more the point.<br>
<br>
Cily <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nobbynoblittlun>Nobbynob Littlun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www2.kalenda.com/andrew/stuff/ezboard-use/alarm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 1:32:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.kalenda.com/andrew/stuff/wizzy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on 2-handers please</span><hr size=1> Maybe VI was silly and has the haste-modified delay as an integer rather than a floating-point decimal, in which case the numbers would get truncated (rounded down) and as such the 1hs's would gain a good bit more from the haste than a 2hs, being a smaller number?<br>
<br>
Oh my god I hope not, that'd be so... lol. I don't think they'd be THAT stupid though. <p>~<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://NobbynobLittlun">Nobbynob Littlun</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aakla2>aakla2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 4:16:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on 2-handers please</span><hr size=1> in some cases 2handers do more dmg then 1handers. but 1handers cause more agro so are better in the long run. <br>
<br>
2handers are good -vs- high reposting mobs. I have started using 2handers in pop -vs- 60+ mobs you keep good agro and you dont get resposted nearlly as much.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lvcm.com/gforce/avs/aakla.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
