<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79585">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79585</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farmatyr1>farmatyr1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 4:30:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on 2-handers please</span><hr size=1> Haste has absolutely no effect on how one weapon does compared to another, unless you have a weapon that gives better haste than whatever you're using otherwise (i.e. ranger, rogue, beastlord epics).<br>
<br>
If one combo does 10% more damage than another, it'll do 10% more damage no matter what your haste is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cily>Cily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 5:30:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jnaggy291392mi/EQ/bubbles1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on 2-handers please</span><hr size=1> Ahh yea, wasn't thinking about the silly haste equation used.<br>
