Cily <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilaara>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 5:41:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4376.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.elchtom.de/Fantasy/f49.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on 2-handers please</span><hr size=1> There are several things to think about.<br>
<br>
1. the more AC the mob has the better for slow 2hers<br>
2. The more the hard hitting Mobs do riposte the better for slow 2hers<br>
3. a slow 2her gereates the same amount of aggro for the try to hit as fast 1hers.<br>
4. fast 1hers have much mor trys to hit so you gain more aggro out of them<br>
5. When youre using 2hers with equal damage delay numbers or better ( 44/44 ... ) they will do more damage than nearly each other weaponcombo in the game, special when youre Level 60 and above ( tripple attack ).<br>
6. 1hers give you a steady stream of hits and damage and so a steady part of aggro.<br>
7. 2hers can give you a real amount of aggro at one time and nearly Zero to another time cause of Misses. ( 6 Misses in a row means 2 Round max with 1hers but always 3 round with a 2her means 2.5 seconds without a damage hit to 7 Seconds without a damage hit.<br>
<br>
